1
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:47,200
Mr. Cheng.

2
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,240
Slow down.

3
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:50,360
Sister Zhuang asked me to take care of you.

4
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:51,680
I have to be responsible for you.

5
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:52,600
If you run so fast,

6
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:54,259
I won't be able to protect you.

7
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:24,680
Two cups.

8
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,120
Mr. Cheng.

9
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:45,000
What are you doing squatting on the floor?

10
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:48,120
It's too clean.

11
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,360
It is indeed very clean.

12
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:55,960
Mr. Cheng,

13
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,560
did you find something else?

14
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:04,000
The victim clearly fell to the ground here.

15
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,200
Then why has such a large area been destroyed?

16
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,920
Mr. Cheng, what's wrong?

17
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:30,800
Wake up.

18
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:31,440
Mr. Cheng.

19
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,170
As expected,

20
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,340
there's a problem.

21
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,360
You really have a problem.

22
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,400
I'll call to send you to the hospital now.

23
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:37,960
No.

24
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,240
I mean,

25
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:42,050
there's a problem with Mu Weijie's death.

26
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,840
What do you mean?

27
00:03:46,079 --> 00:03:48,680
If you want to know the cause of the victim's death,

28
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:51,280
the most direct way is to empathize with him.

29
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,440
That is to say,

30
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,880
you had a heart attack just now

31
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:57,140
because you empathized with the victim?

32
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,880
So what did you find?

33
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,000
Someone came in.

34
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,010
Captain Zhuang,

35
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:08,810
we found something.

36
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,520
The surface of the body is too clean,

37
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:14,080
including under the fingernails.

38
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:16,140
It must have been cleaned by someone.

39
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:18,440
It seems the victim wasn't alone at the scene.

40
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:20,240
I don't see anyone here either.

41
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:21,399
Shh.

42
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:24,000
He came.

43
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,680
Who was here?

44
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:29,400
What did he come for?

45
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:32,920
Mu Weijie died of a heart attack.

46
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:36,760
But what happened before he fell

47
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:38,920
that made the scene so messy?

48
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,520
He was hiding.

49
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:44,140
That person must have wanted to kill him.

50
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:07,840
Let me go.

51
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,080
Mr. Cheng.

52
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:20,840
You mean someone hit Mu Weijie last night.

53
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:22,160
But

54
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,240
there were no wounds on his body.

55
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:27,240
An accident happened.

56
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:29,440
On the fallen easel at the scene,

57
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:31,700
I found strike marks from a wooden stick.

58
00:05:32,159 --> 00:05:36,120
And we extracted crystallized salt stains from the victim's body.

59
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,200
It's sweat.

60
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:39,200
Right.

61
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:40,400
It is sweat.

62
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:42,040
That makes sense.

63
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:45,440
He sweated a lot before he died.

64
00:05:46,159 --> 00:05:48,760
Plus the smash marks on the easel.

65
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:52,600
I guess the victim had a conflict with someone before he died.

66
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,530
That person hit the fallen easel with a wooden stick.

67
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:59,600
To cover up the evidence,

68
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:03,120
he cleaned all the traces on the body's surface.

69
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,160
You guys haven't left yet.

70
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:09,080
We made a new discovery during this investigation.

71
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:09,720
Tell us.

72
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:12,290
Have some water.

73
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,410
What discovery?

74
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:21,360
There was another person at the scene.

75
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:22,620
He attacked Mu Weijie,

76
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:23,960
and then ran away.

77
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,720
So you guys found out too.

78
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:28,600
You found out too?

79
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,240
It's not me who found out.

80
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:32,280
It's us.

81
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:34,680
We really have to thank Shao for this.

82
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,460
Take a look.

83
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:39,320
On the evidence at the scene,

84
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:41,840
I found some slight bump marks.

85
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:44,960
He also found a lot of sweat stains on the victim,

86
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:47,960
and that this person had cleaned the victim's body.

87
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,240
Shao,

88
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,280
you're amazing.

89
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,440
Of course.

90
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:53,880
So,

91
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:56,080
that person must have broken in with a weapon,

92
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:57,320
attacked the victim,

93
00:06:57,720 --> 00:07:00,000
before having a chance to cause any harm.

94
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:02,200
The victim had a heart attack out of fear

95
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,330
and died on the spot.

96
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,800
That's exactly what Mr. Cheng said.

97
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:06,200
Right?

98
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:06,840
Right.

99
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,960
Impressive, young man.

100
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,400
I think

101
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,800
the murder weapon

102
00:07:11,880 --> 00:07:15,040
was probably those discarded picture frames scattered at the door.

103
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:15,500
Agreed.

104
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:16,820
I noticed that too.

105
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:21,040
The most easily accessible things in the studio are these picture frames.

106
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:23,600
And they also match the scratches on the easel.

107
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:26,960
But I checked all the surveillance near the crime scene last night,

108
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:28,960
and no one appeared carrying a weapon.

109
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:32,440
Could it be that the frame was discarded in a surveillance blind spot?

110
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:34,720
Then we'll have to use the most primitive method

111
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,080
to rule things out.

112
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:37,370
Mr. Fang.

113
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:40,440
Take your men to primarily check the trash cans,

114
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:42,600
green belts, and construction sites.

115
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:46,040
Focus on the areas with surveillance blind spots.

116
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:50,000
If we can find this wooden frame strip,

117
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,720
we'll be one step closer to the truth.

118
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:55,360
Come on.

119
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,040
Qiaoyue, it's me.

120
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:10,160
I'm back.

121
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,520
Why are you here?

122
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,160
I wanted to see you.

123
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:16,680
You... you are a murderer now.

124
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:17,810
You killed someone.

125
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:20,040
Why are you seeing me instead of hiding?

126
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,560
I didn't kill anyone.

127
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,760
Besides, where can I go?

128
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,640
Did you give a statement to the investigation bureau?

129
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:29,370
You didn't sell me out, did you?

130
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:31,080
How could I sell you out?

131
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,039
And if I sold you out,

132
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,559
how could you be here?

133
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:36,370
Did you go to the studio?

134
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:37,919
Did you?

135
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:39,440
I'm telling you.

136
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,900
The police are very smart.

137
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:42,400
If you've been to the studio,

138
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:43,840
they will definitely find your fingerprints

139
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,240
and your tracks.

140
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,280
Chances are,

141
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:48,080
they will find you in a day or two.

142
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:48,920
If you trust me,

143
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:50,450
you need to leave right now.

144
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:52,360
I'll say it again.

145
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,400
I didn't kill anyone.

146
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,640
I didn't even touch him.

147
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:56,680
I believe you,

148
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:58,410
but will the police believe it?

149
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,400
Qiaoyue.

150
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:02,260
Don't touch me.

151
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:04,620
We have already broken up.

152
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:06,120
Break up?

153
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,200
Who said we broke up?

154
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,330
I didn't agree to it.

155
00:09:11,680 --> 00:09:14,680
Have you ever been sincere to me all these years?

156
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:15,880
And now you say

157
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,000
you don't agree?

158
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,320
Qiaoyue.

159
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:22,840
Qiaoyue, don't forget

160
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,440
who I went to the studio for.

161
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:26,560
Did I ask you to go?

162
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:28,800
Qiaoyue, promise me,

163
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:31,640
you won't tell anyone about this.

164
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:33,400
If you dare betray me,

165
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,730
I will never let you off.

166
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,160
Xiaoyue,

167
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:39,040
is that you?

168
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:40,370
Mind your own business.

169
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:42,320
It's me, Mom.

170
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,800
Where were you?

171
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,160
Why are you back so late?

172
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,160
Mr. Mu is dead.

173
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:51,160
Mr. Mu is dead?

174
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:52,200
How did he die?

175
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,640
You have nothing to do with it, right?

176
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:55,480
What could it have to do with me?

177
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,560
I was just cooperating with the investigation.

178
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:59,000
All my studio classmates went.

179
00:09:59,000 --> 00:09:59,880
Don't worry.

180
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:01,560
Besides, the police said

181
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,770
it was an accidental death.

182
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:07,160
Hurry, go inside.

183
00:10:07,160 --> 00:10:08,360
I'm coming up.

184
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:53,120
Stop! Don't run!

185
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:53,920
This way!

186
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:55,400
This way!

187
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:56,000
Don't run!

188
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:56,440
Stop!

189
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,100
Don't move!

190
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:03,320
Stop!

191
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:04,920
Stop!

192
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:06,040
Don't run!

193
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:08,320
Trying to run?

194
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:10,760
Why are you arresting me?

195
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:11,480
Shut up!

196
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:12,600
Take him away.

197
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:13,240
Go.

198
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:14,880
Behave.

199
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:15,240
Go.

200
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,360
Trying to run?

201
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:20,850
Captain Zhuang,

202
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,050
that was brilliant!

203
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:23,320
Not bad.

204
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:30,520
Officer,

205
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,200
did you make a mistake?

206
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,640
You're wronging an innocent person.

207
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:34,440
Let me go.

208
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:36,240
You've really got the wrong guy.

209
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:38,680
Stop arguing.

210
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:41,520
We wouldn't invite you here without evidence.

211
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:42,320
Besides, if you don't have a guilty conscience,

212
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,180
why did you run?

213
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:44,880
I didn't run.

214
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:47,040
I just wanted to catch a ride home quickly.

215
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:48,280
I'm not a Mancheng local.

216
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:49,520
Watch your language.

217
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:52,600
Officer.

218
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:55,600
Is it a crime to catch a ride home?

219
00:11:56,760 --> 00:11:57,690
Get to the point.

220
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:01,460
Where were you between 5 p.m. and 7 p.m. on Thursday?

221
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,600
I don't remember.

222
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:05,800
How could I remember so clearly?

223
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:06,840
I'm very busy.

224
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:09,240
Let me help you remember.

225
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,260
You were at Doukou Studio, right?

226
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:13,940
What happened with Mu Weijie?

227
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:19,320
I don't know what you're talking about.

228
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:21,040
Stop wasting your time on me.

229
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:23,370
You should hurry up and catch the bad guys.

230
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,280
Officer.

231
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:25,280
What time is it now?

232
00:12:25,280 --> 00:12:26,840
I need to catch my ride home.

233
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:29,500
Look familiar?

234
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:31,840
Then can you explain to me

235
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:34,040
why your fingerprints are on this?
